    • Method Detail

      • assertDisjunction

        public InequalitySystemSolver assertDisjunction(InequalitySystem... disjunction)
        Assert a new set of inequality systems. When called with a parameter like 
        { A, B }
        where A and B are inequality systems, this adds the requirement that either A or B have to be satisfied to solutions.
        Parameters:
        disjunction - Contains a disjunction of inequality systems.
        Returns:
        This solver instance

      • push

        public InequalitySystemSolver push()
        Push the current solver state onto a stack. All following modifications can be undone via pop().
        Returns:
        This solver instance

      • pop

        public InequalitySystemSolver pop()
        Pop the last disjunction that was added from the solver context. This undoes the effects of the last call to push().
        Returns:
        This solver instance

      • findSolution

        public java.util.List<java.math.BigInteger> findSolution()
        Calculate a solution to the conjunction of disjunctions that were added to this solver.
        Returns:
        A solution to the systems or an empty list if unsolvable
